  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want the unread count to persist after restarting the app so that the count is meaninful for me.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: After I read all the messages in a public chat and navigate to the home screen, and restart the app, the unread messages count has the old value, instead of showing that all messages are read.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Create a new account and join a stale public chat containing a large number of unread messages (let's say > 50, exemplified with `#test` public chat below):\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/138074/41292431-daf0864e-6e52-11e8-99c9-862c63fcd18f.png)\r\n\r\n- While the app is retrieving messages from mailserver, go back to home screen (make sure that the unread badge is visible for the chat)\r\n- Go to the OS home screen\r\n- Kill the Status app by swiping it away in the running app list\r\n- Start app again and sign in to the same account\r\n- Enter the public chat screen and scroll up until all are considered read\r\n- Go back to the main screen (notice that unread badge has disappeared from `#test`):\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/138074/41292419-cd55795e-6e52-11e8-953b-08225ac80389.png)\r\n\r\n- Go to the OS home screen\r\n- Kill the Status app by swiping it away in the running app list\r\n- Open Status again and sign in to the same account (notice that unread badge has reappeared for `#test`):\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/138074/41292431-daf0864e-6e52-11e8-99c9-862c63fcd18f.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\n\r\nApp shows that no unread messages exist for that public chat.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\n\r\nApp still shows the old number of unread messages for that public chat.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: Nightly 0.9.19 build 6044\r\n* Operating System: Android",
